etorical force, and metafictional intentionality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aFictionxHistory and criticism. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Subjects & Themes / Historical Events .2bisacsh1 aFox, Dian.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174529440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501745294423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501745294/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK